  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>This release addresses key fixes across several areas, including the Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT), accepting partial cash payments, receiving Purchase Orders, and Import/Export functionality.</p><h3 id=\"RepairQ1.22.1-CashTerminalsandPayments\">Cash Terminals and Payments</h3><ul><li><p>Implemented an automatic Workstation Key reassignment to maintain active VCT sessions. This update prevents issues where the VCT may unintentionally close or un-assign itself, allowing users to continue their work without requiring a log out and log back in.</p></li><li><p>Resolved an issue where users encountered an erroneous &quot;Float amount is set to $0.00&quot; error, which prevented VCT opening or reconciliation. This update also fixes an issue where the cash reconciliation report was missing, ensuring a smoother VCT process and accurate reporting.</p></li><li><p>We fixed an issue where adding a partial cash payment incorrectly set the ticket balance to $0. Now, only the entered payment amount will be applied, ensuring the remaining balance is correctly reflected.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"RepairQ1.22.1-PurchaseOrders\">Purchase Orders</h3><ul><li><p>We resolved an issue where some purchase order items were not receiving a timestamp when marked as received, which caused errors for users processing purchase orders.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"RepairQ1.22.1-ImportsandExports\">Imports and Exports</h3><ul><li><p>We resolved an issue where queued import and export tasks showed no records after completion. Previously, exports generated a success email, but the link directed users to a broken page, and imports consistently failed. Both issues have now been addressed for smoother task processing.</p></li></ul><p />",
      "representation": "export_view",
